                            <comment id="14646363" author="jira-bot" created="Wed, 29 Jul 2015 16:35:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1693310 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1693310&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1693310&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2906&quot; title=&quot;NullPointerException in PDFStreamEngine.showText&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2906&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2906&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: save textLineMatrix and textMatrix before showing a glyph to avoid it being lost in recursion&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14646366" author="tilman" created="Wed, 29 Jul 2015 16:37:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The bug happened because the text was rendered with a pattern that had a text within, so the textMatrix was lost in recursion. It renders nicely now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14648042" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 30 Jul 2015 18:07:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1693464 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1693464&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1693464&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2906&quot; title=&quot;NullPointerException in PDFStreamEngine.showText&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2906&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2906&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: don&apos;t reset matrix when saving it&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14648046" author="lehmi" created="Thu, 30 Jul 2015 18:09:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; Your change introduced a regression (some tests are failing), as you reset both matrix values when saving it. I&apos;ve removed the reset part and now everything works, rendering of the attached pdf and all tests are green.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14648120" author="tilman" created="Thu, 30 Jul 2015 18:47:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks + sorry. How it happened: originally it was a 2-line-change which built with test (I think). Then saw a piece of code elsewhere that was doing more (saving another element, and assigning an identity matrix). I still rendering-tested that one, but didn&apos;t build-test it &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14648140" author="lehmi" created="Thu, 30 Jul 2015 19:10:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No need to worry, that&apos;s what tests are for &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
